The paper presents a new approach to automatic inference in probabilistic programming using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of attention mechanisms is also a key aspect of the proposed method, which is a popular area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image processing (cs.CV) and the optimization of proposal distributions (cs.NE), which are also relevant sub-categories in computer science.
